ogram_sample()` for the same purpose. Consensus reached on MVP: add a warning when `get_type(predicted) == \"integer\"`. Discussion also suggested possibly removing `log_score` from default metrics for sample forecasts. | None. All building blocks exist (`get_type()`, `cli_warn()`, pattern established in `bias_sample()`). | Add `get_type(predicted)` check to `logs_sample()` that emits `cli_warn()` when predictions are integer-valued. Optionally move `log_score` out of the default metric list in `get_metrics.forecast_sample()`. Add targeted tests. | [ ] | [ ] | — | [ ] |\n| 356 | Documentation: Create a vignette for interactions with other packages | documentation | 2023-10-26 | documentation | low | medium | partially | Still relevant. No interoperability vignette exists. Deprecated-visualisations vignette mentions hubVis. Hubverse integration moved to external `hubEvals` package (#605, closed). No conversion functions for external packages exist in scoringutils. `as_forecast_*` S3 generics provide extension points for external packages. ~2.5 years old with no progress. | Related to #385 (data transformation for other packages), #852 (custom forecast class workflow), #983 (`.data.frame` methods). | Create a vignette documenting how to use scoringutils with common external packages (hubverse via hubEvals, Stan output, yardstick). Focus on showing the `as_forecast_*()` S3 extension mechanism and practical conversion patterns. Requires editorial decisions on scope and which packages to feature. | N/A | N/A | — | N/A |\n| 353 | Documentation: Create a vignette that details the different inputs and internal workings of scoringutils | documentation | 2023-10-26 | documentation | medium | large | partially | Still relevant but heavily overlapping with #546, #759, #852. The deleted `scoringutils.Rmd` vignette (PR #836) covered 3 of 4 bullet points; replacement was never written. README \"Quick start\" section partially addresses input formats and workflow. The \"create your own class\" bullet is blocked by prerequisite S3 refactors (#889, #888, #885). Package currently has no introductory or architecture vignette. | Tightly coupled with #546 (simplify getting started) and #759 (replace deleted vignette). \"Create your own class\" aspect depends on #852, blocked by #889, #888, #885. | Consider consolidating with #546 and #759 into a single effort to write a new introductory vignette covering input formats, the `as_forecast_*()` / `score()` workflow, and forecast object anatomy. Defer \"create your own class\" section until S3 extensibility refactors are complete. | N/A | N/A | — | N/A |\n| 338 | Discussion: Define implementation for metrics which work for different forecast types | help wanted, question, Breaking change | 2023-10-22 | discussion | low | medium | no | Partially addressed by #832 (`get_metrics()` now S3). The remaining question is whether individual metric functions (e.g., `bias_sample`/`bias_quantile`) should also become S3 generics for standalone use. Practical need is low since `score()` already dispatches correctly via `get_metrics.<class>`. 6 conceptual metrics span 2+ forecast types with type-suffixed names. | #832 (done). Related to #455 (vector returns), #941 (rethink `score()` S3). No blockers. | Consider downgrading from \"Breaking change\" since S3 wrappers could be additive. If pursued, create `bias()`, `overprediction()`, `underprediction()`, `dispersion()`, `ae_median()`, `logs()` as S3 generics dispatching on forecast class, keeping suffixed functions as implementations. Defer to future major release. | N/A | N/A | — | N/A |\n| 329 | Add additional documentation for `crps_sample()`, `logs_sample()` and `dss_sample()` | package improvement | 2023-09-15 | documentation | low | small | partially | Still relevant. Formulas exist in the vignette (`scoring-rules.Rmd`) but have not been ported to the roxygen docs for these three functions. Other functions in the same file (e.g., `bias_sample`, `pit_histogram_sample`) already have formula-rich roxygen documentation via `\\deqn{}`, providing a clear template. `dss_sample()` is worst — almost no description beyond \"wrapper.\" | None. Standalone documentation task. | Add `\\deqn{}` mathematical formulas and expanded descriptions to roxygen docs of `crps_sample()`, `logs_sample()`, and `dss_sample()` in `R/metrics-sample.R`. Adapt formulas from the existing vignette content. `dss_sample()` needs the most work. | N/A | N/A | — | N/A |\n| 289 | Add support for comparing two distributions | | 2023-07-12 | feature | low | large | no | Still relevant. Zero implementation exists. The entire package architecture assumes scoring against scalar observations. No distribution comparison functions in codebase or in `scoringRules` dependency. Requires fundamental design decisions: new forecast class, new metric functions, and integration approach. 2.5+ years old with zero comments. Filed as an aspirational idea. | Related to #852 (custom forecast class workflow), #889/#888 (S3 extensibility). No issues depend on this. | Design and implement a new forecast class for distribution-to-distribution comparison with associated metrics (energy distance, KL divergence, Wasserstein distance). Should be deferred until S3 extensibility infrastructure (#852, #889, #888) is complete. | N/A | N/A | — | N/A |\n| 286 | Extension covering idees in \"Model Diagnostics and Forecast Evaluation for Quantiles\" | enhancement, feature request | 2023-05-03 | feature | medium | large | no | Still relevant. None of the three proposed features (consistency-banded coverage plots, Murphy diagrams, CORP reliability diagrams) are implemented. Basic coverage plots and PIT histograms exist but lack the statistical rigor proposed. Paper's code could serve as starting point. ~3 years old with no progress. Design decisions needed on scope, API, and potential new dependencies (e.g., `reliabilitydiag` R package). | Thematically related to #49 (calibration plotting improvement). No hard blockers. @jbracher is already a scoringutils contributor. | Implement three new diagnostic tools from Bracher et al.: (1) add consistency bands and confidence intervals to existing coverage plots, (2) create `murphy_diagram()` function and plot, (3) create CORP reliability diagram function. Consider addressing #49 simultaneously. | N/A | N/A | — | N/A |\n| 267 | How to score literature/other resources | documentation, help wanted | 2023-02-13 | documentation | low | small | no | Still relevant. Function-level `@references` tags exist across 8 R files, and the scoring-rules vignette has a .bib with 7 papers. However, the agreed-upon deliverable — a standalone, discoverable vignette summarizing scoring methodology and linking to key literature — has not been created. Two vignettes referenced in the README (\"metric-details\", \"scoring-forecasts-directly\") do not exist on disk. ~3 years old. | None blocking. Related to #758 (scoring rules vignette), #789 (customization docs), #666 (update paper). | Create a short standalone vignette summarizing scoring methodology and consolidating all referenced literature into one discoverable place. Link to the full paper and relevant external resources. Also fix the broken vignette links in the README. Requires editorial decisions on content. | N/A | N/A | — | N/A |\n| 193 | Add more metrics to assess sharpness of forecasts in a sample format | feature request, implementation-ready | 2022-02-16 | feature | low | small | yes | Still relevant. `mad_sample()` is the only dedicated sharpness metric. SD and IQR (specifically requested) are not implemented. Both are trivial to add following the `mad_sample()` pattern (data-independent, apply function row-wise over predicted matrix). `dispersion_sample()` (CRPS component) also measures spread but is observation-dependent. `scoringRules` provides no additional sharpness measures. | None. Self-contained addition following existing `mad_sample()` pattern. | Implement `sd_sample()` and `iqr_sample()` in `R/metrics-sample.R` following the `mad_sample()` pattern. Add both to the default metric list in `get_metrics.forecast_sample()`. Add tests, documentation, and NAMESPACE exports. | [ ] | [ ] | — | [ ] |\n| 49 | Improve calibration plotting | enhancement, feature request | 2020-07-25 | feature | low | medium | no | Partially addressed. PIT histograms exist via `get_pit_histogram()` (covering item 1 approximately). Items 2 (ACF of PIT values) and 3 (marginal calibration plot) are completely unimplemented. True Talagrand/verification rank histogram also not implemented as a distinct tool. Maintainer said \"no active plan, but nice to have.\" 5+ years old. | Thematically overlaps with #286 (advanced calibration diagnostics). No hard blockers. | Three remaining items: (1) implement verification rank histogram for ensemble/sample forecasts, (2) implement ACF computation/plot for PIT values, (3) implement marginal calibration plot. Consider consolidating with #286 into a single calibration diagnostics tracking issue. | N/A | N/A | — | N/A |\n| 37 | Add Diebold Mariano test | enhancement, good first issue, help wanted, feature request | 2020-06-20 | feature | low | small | partially | Still relevant. No DM test implementation exists. `compare_forecasts()` in `R/pairwise-comparisons.R` already has a clean `test_type` dispatch pattern (Wilcoxon and permutation). The DM test's main value-add is proper handling of autocorrelated score differences common in time-series forecasting. Open since 2020 with maintainer agreement but explicitly deferred. | Dependency of #1055 (model confidence sets). Related to #750 (p-value refactor), #769 (pairwise comparison arguments), #1022 (two-model case). | Add `\"dm\"` as a new `test_type` option in `compare_forecasts()`. Self-implement the DM test statistic (preferred over adding `forecast` dependency) with Newey-West HAC variance estimator. Add tests and documentation. Coordinate naming and autocorrelation lag handling with maintainers. | N/A | N/A | — | N/A |\n\nTRIAGE_COMPLETE","numLines":131,"startLine":1,"totalLines":131}}}
